block Slide_In_Panel_Content
	.summary.cd
		h4.cd Summary
		p.cd At the University of Maryland, I am actively working with 4 fellow senior bioengineering students on an immersive experience device for pediatric patients. Currently, when an MRI is needed, pediatric patients are given anesthesia; however, there is a growing body of literature suggesting that this practice can lead to short term and possibly long term neurological deficits, along with additional cost, risks for respiratory issues, and other immediate concerns. Our approach is to create a device that follows the user from the hallway/waiting room to inside the MRI and all the way back out.
